<subSubSection id="C347657E9D69FFDEFC87FA8332A4F8FC" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE236F59D69FFDEFC87FA8332C5FA1B" blockId="21.[813,1422,1389,1482]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC87FA83352BFA54" bold="true" box="[813,1040,1389,1413]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Material examined.</emphasis>
Middle slopes on 
<collectionCode id="ED4CAE309D69FFDEFB76FA8035CEFA54" box="[1244,1269,1390,1413]" country="Austria" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15588" name="Naturhistorisches Museum Wien" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="Herbarium">W</collectionCode>
side of Cerro Pirre; 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6950329D69FFDEFCC5FA6032F1FA76" box="[879,970,1422,1447]" degrees="07" direction="north" minutes="57" orientation="latitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" precision="925" value="7.95">07°57′N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="EE6950329D69FFDEFC7EFA60357BFA76" box="[980,1088,1422,1447]" degrees="077" direction="west" minutes="46" orientation="longitude" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" precision="925" value="-77.76667">077°46′W</geoCoordinate>
; 
<quantity id="4CA59B109D69FFDEFBE0FA6135FFFA76" box="[1098,1220,1423,1447]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.55" metricValueMax="7.6" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" unit="m" value="655.0" valueMax="760.0" valueMin="550.0">550–760 m</quantity>
; 
<date id="FFE310359D69FFDEFB64FA7E346DFA79" box="[1230,1366,1424,1448]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" value="1988-06-28">28 Jun. 1988</date>
; 
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFACAFA7E328EFA18" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">
<collectionCode id="ED4CAE309D69FFDEFACAFA7E3448FA76" box="[1376,1395,1424,1447]" name="Tavera, Department of Geology and Geophysics" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">T</collectionCode>
. 
<collectionCode id="ED4CAE309D69FFDEFADCFA7E34B2FA76" box="[1398,1417,1424,1447]" country="Germany" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15534" name="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Zentraleinrichtung der Freien Universitaet" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="Herbarium">B</collectionCode>
. Croat 68888
</emphasis>
(
<collectionCode id="ED4CAE309D69FFDEFC69FA5C32C9FA1B" box="[963,1010,1458,1482]" country="USA" lsid="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:15859" name="Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="Herbarium">MO</collectionCode>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE236F59D69FFDEFC87FA0D32A4F8FC" blockId="21.[811,1421,1507,1837]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC87FA0D3261F9CC" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC87FA0D32F5FA2A" bold="true" box="[813,974,1507,1531]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Identification.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D769D69FFDEFC4AFA0D35D3FA2A" authorityName="Madison" authorityYear="1759" baseAuthorityName="Mast." box="[992,1256,1507,1531]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Chlorospatha" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mirabilis">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC4AFA0D35D3FA2A" box="[992,1256,1507,1531]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Chlorospatha mirabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized
</emphasis>
by its terrestrial habit, milky sap, trilobed or tri- sect leaves, usually maculate, long inflorescences, and spadices with a very long sterile region (approximately one-third of the total). By the combination of characters mentioned, this species has no similar species on Cerro Pirre, although in the field could be confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5D4D769D69FFDEFC87F93F35E3F938" authority="(Jacq.) Schott" authorityName="Schott" baseAuthorityName="Jacq." box="[813,1240,1745,1769]" class="Liliopsida" family="Araceae" genus="Philodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Alismatales" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tripartitum">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC87F93F3504F938" box="[813,1087,1745,1769]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Philodendron tripartitum</emphasis>
(Jacq.) Schott
</taxonomicName>
, which differs by having colorless or reddish latex and fused stamens as synandria.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C347657E9D69FFDEFC87F8A932F6F7FA" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BE236F59D69FFDEFC87F8A932F6F7FA" blockId="21.[812,1421,1863,2091]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">
<emphasis id="B929EAE79D69FFDEFC87F8A93559F88E" bold="true" box="[813,1122,1863,1887]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Distribution and ecology.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F34A76659D69FFDEFBD9F8A935E4F88E" box="[1139,1247,1863,1887]" name="Colombia" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34A76659D69FFDEFB59F8A93474F88E" box="[1267,1359,1863,1887]" name="Ecuador" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="F34A76659D69FFDEFC87F88432BDF850" box="[813,902,1898,1921]" name="Panama" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Panama</collectingCountry>
. In 
<collectingCountry id="F34A76659D69FFDEFC1BF8843531F850" box="[945,1034,1898,1921]" name="Panama" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Panama</collectingCountry>
, the populations of this species are found only in 
<collectingRegion id="4999F8179D69FFDEFC6FF8653542F872" box="[965,1145,1931,1955]" country="Panama" name="Darien" pageId="21" pageNumber="672">Darién Province</collectingRegion>
. The collection data from the only specimen of Cerro Pirre indicate that it grows in the evergreen forest, between 550 and 
<specimenCount id="9D5BFD7C9D69FFDEFB44F8213402F837" box="[1262,1337,1999,2023]" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" type="generic">
<quantity id="4CA59B109D69FFDEFB44F821340FF837" box="[1262,1332,1999,2023]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.6" pageId="21" pageNumber="672" unit="m" value="760.0">760 m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
During the samplings it was not possible to observe individuals of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
